-- 0011 was originally a `projects` table rebuild generated by drizzle to
-- enforce NOT NULL on `subscription_status`, `cancel_at_period_end`, and
-- `billing_interval`. Those columns were already added with `NOT NULL DEFAULT`
-- by 0008_billing.sql, so the rebuild is a no-op against any DB that has
-- 0008 applied — it just churns the table.
--
-- The rebuild also failed on D1 in practice: the SQLite "create __new_projects
-- → INSERT … SELECT → DROP projects → RENAME" dance trips on FK references
-- from gates/configs/experiments/etc., and `PRAGMA foreign_keys=OFF` is
-- silently ignored inside D1's per-migration transaction. `defer_foreign_keys`
-- bypasses the FK check but then the COMMIT trips on a generic D1 internal
-- error (code 7500) — likely the per-statement-breakpoint batch semantics.
--
-- Since the data result is "no schema change," we replace the body with a
-- no-op that succeeds and gets recorded in `d1_migrations`. Future migrations
-- proceed normally.
SELECT 1;
